{#

    Go Top Button
    -------------

    A fixed button that appears after scrolling down and scrolls the page to a target element by ID.

    `id`: the HTML id of the target element to scroll to when the button is clicked.

    Content
    -------
    Is used as the button's tooltip (`title` attribute).

    Usage
    -----

    To create a "go to top" button linked to an element with id "top":

        <header id="top">...</header>
        ...
        <ui.GoTopButton id="top">Back to Top</ui.GoTopButton>

#}

<a href="#{{id}}" id="go-top-button" title="{{content}}"
    class="hidden fixed bottom-5 right-5 z-50 
        bg-white text-purple-600 w-12 h-12 
        flex items-center justify-center rounded 
        hover:bg-gray-100">
    â†‘
</a>
<script>
    const btn = document.getElementById("go-top-button");
    window.addEventListener("scroll", () => {
        btn.classList.toggle("hidden", window.scrollY <= 300);
    });
</script>